==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bowie knife
<hw>Bow"ie knife`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A knife with a strong blade
from ten to fifteen inches long, and double-edged near the point; --
used as a hunting knife, and formerly as a weapon in the southwestern
part of the United States. It was named from its inventor,
<person>Colonel James <etsep>Bowie</etsep></person>. Also, by extension,
any large sheath knife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bowing</ent>⟦br⟧
